---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Noorum Paalum | Classic Naga Offering | Nagayakshi Temple">

  <section class="pooja-hero">
    <div class="pooja-hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="pooja-hero-content">
      <span class="pooja-badge">Monthly Ritual</span>
      <h1>Noorum Paalum</h1>
      <p class="pooja-tagline">Kerala&#8217;s most sacred Naga offering — rice and milk presented with devotion to the divine serpents</p>
      <div class="pooja-quick-info">
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Frequency</span>
          <span class="info-value">Monthly / As Needed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-info-item">
          <span class="info-label">Duration</span>
          <span class="info-value">1&#8211;2 hours</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-ctas">
        <a href="https://forms.gle/C3eQViaTHURBS48v7" class="btn-primary-gold" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enquire</a>
        <a href="#details" class="btn-secondary-outline">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pooja-section" id="details">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>What is Noorum Paalum?</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <p class="intro-text">
            Noorum Paalum (Malayalam: നൂറും പാലും) is one of the most ancient and widespread
            serpent-deity offerings in Kerala, literally meaning "rice flour and milk." This
            offering is presented to Naga deities at Sarpa Kavu (serpent groves) to pacify
            Sarpa Dosha, invoke blessings for childless couples, remove obstacles to marriage,
            and seek the Naga deity&#8217;s protection for the household and all its members.
            It is the foundational offering upon which all other Naga rituals are built.
          </p>
          <h3>The Significance of Noorum Paalum</h3>
          <p>
            Rice (Nooram) and milk (Paalum) are the two most primal offerings in Kerala&#8217;s
            Naga tradition. Rice symbolizes the earth&#8217;s abundance and the devotee&#8217;s
            surrender of the harvest to the divine. Milk, drawn from the sacred cow, represents
            purity, nourishment, and the flowing grace of the deity. Together, they form the
            simplest yet most complete offering one can make to the Naga.
          </p>
          <div class="variant-cards">
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>1. Basic Noorum Paalum</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> Regular Naga propitiation<br>
                <strong>Includes:</strong> Rice flour offering, milk pouring, flowers, lamps,
                and basic Naga mantra recitation at the serpent shrine
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>2. Noorum Paalum with Payasabali</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> Enhanced blessings for progeny or marriage<br>
                <strong>Includes:</strong> Noorum Paalum combined with sweet rice pudding
                (payasam) offered to the Naga deity for sweetness and fulfillment of wishes
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="variant-card">
              <h4>3. Saparivara Noorum Paalum</h4>
              <p>
                <strong>For:</strong> Comprehensive household Naga blessings<br>
                <strong>Includes:</strong> Full Naga family worship with Noorum Paalum offered
                to all eight Naga deities (Ashta Nagas) and their consorts
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="info-box">
            <h4>Quick Facts</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Kerala&#8217;s most common Naga offering</li>
              <li>Can be performed monthly on Ayilyam</li>
              <li>Suitable for all Sarpa Dosha types</li>
              <li>Simple yet highly efficacious</li>
              <li>Ideal for first-time Naga worshippers</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box highlight">
            <h4>Best For</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Sarpa Dosha relief</li>
              <li>Childlessness &amp; progeny</li>
              <li>Delayed or blocked marriage</li>
              <li>Skin disorders (Naga-related)</li>
              <li>Household protection</li>
              <li>Regular Naga worship</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tradition-section">
    <div class="pooja-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Sacred Origins</span>
        <h2>The Tradition of Noorum Paalum</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="tradition-story">
        <div class="story-image">
          <img src="/images/Noorum%20Paalum.jpeg" alt="Noorum Paalum offering at Naga shrine">
        </div>
        <div class="story-content">
          <h3>The Original Naga Offering</h3>
          <p>
            In Kerala&#8217;s ancient Naga worship tradition, the Sarpa Kavu (sacred serpent
            groves) adjacent to family homesteads were the primary sites of Naga veneration.
            These groves, undisturbed by human activity, were believed to be the dwelling places
            of the Naga deities who protected the family land. The daily or monthly Noorum Paalum
            maintained this sacred relationship between the family and the resident Naga.
          </p>
          <p>
            Over centuries, as urbanization reduced the Sarpa Kavus, the practice moved into
            dedicated Naga temples like Sree Pulikkal Vishwanagayakshi Temple, where the same
            ancient tradition is maintained with complete ritual authenticity under the guidance
            of Ambotti Thampuran.
          </p>
          <div class="scripture-quote">
            <p>
              &#8220;May the Nagas, who dwell in the earth, water, and sky, accept this
              offering of Noorum Paalum and grant long life, prosperity, and children
              to the devotee who offers with a pure heart.&#8221;
            </p>
            <span class="quote-attribution">&#8212; Kerala Naga Pooja Tradition, Oral Lineage</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tradition-variants">
        <h3>Ritual Details</h3>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>Auspicious Timing</h4>
          <p>
            Noorum Paalum is most potent when performed on Ayilyam Nakshathra (the serpent
            star), which occurs monthly. It is also performed on Pooyam, Atham, and on the
            Naga Panchami festival. In cases of urgent need, it may be performed on any day
            auspicious to the individual&#8217;s nakshatra.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="variant-detail">
          <h4>What Happens During the Ritual</h4>
          <p>
            The priest prepares the offering vessels with rice flour mixed with water into a
            smooth paste, which is shaped into symbolic serpent forms. Fresh milk is poured
            over the Naga shrine. Specific Naga stotras and the Sarpa Sukta from the Atharva
            Veda are recited. The ritual concludes with a lamp offering (deepa aradhana)
            and the distribution of prasadam including turmeric, flowers, and sacred ash.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="booking-cta-section" id="booking">
    <div class="booking-cta-container">
      <h2>Enquire About Noorum Paalum</h2>
      <p>
        Most auspicious on <strong>Ayilyam Nakshathra</strong> &#8212; performed monthly<br>
        Also available on request for any auspicious day
      </p>
      <div class="booking-cta-buttons">
        <a href="https://forms.gle/C3eQViaTHURBS48v7" class="btn-primary-gold btn-large" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enquire Now</a>
        <a href="tel:+919946373522" class="btn-secondary-outline">Call: +91 9946373522</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
.pooja-hero {
  position: relative; min-height: 70vh; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  background: linear-gradient(rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.75), rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.9)), url('/images/Noorum%20Paalum.jpeg') center/cover;
  padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem; text-align: center;
}
.pooja-hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, rgba(212, 165, 116, 0.12) 0%, transparent 60%); }
.pooja-hero-content { max-width: 900px; position: relative; z-index: 10; }
.pooja-badge { display: inline-block; background: var(--laterite-red); color: white; padding: 0.5rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.pooja-hero h1 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 4.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-shadow: 0 2px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.5); }
.pooja-tagline { font-size: 1.35rem; color: var(--bg-alt); margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.pooja-quick-info { display: flex; gap: 2rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 3rem; padding: 1.8rem 2rem; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); backdrop-filter: blur(10px); border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2); }
.quick-info-item { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 0.4rem; }
.info-label { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #ffd285; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; }
.info-value { font-size: 1.15rem; color: white; font-weight: 600; }
.hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.pooja-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-base); }
.pooja-container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }
.section-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.section-header h2 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); }
.content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
.content-main { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.9; }
.intro-text { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--laterite-dark); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
.content-main h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--laterite-red); margin: 2.5rem 0 1.2rem; }
.content-main p { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.variant-cards { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.variant-card { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); }
.variant-card h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.variant-card p { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
.content-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; }
.info-box { background: var(--bg-alt); padding: 1.8rem; border-radius: 10px; border: 2px solid #e8c9a0; }
.info-box.highlight { background: var(--laterite-dark); border-color: var(--gold); }
.info-box h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.info-box.highlight h4 { color: #ffd285; }
.info-box ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
.info-box li { padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.05); }
.info-box.highlight li { color: var(--bg-alt); border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }
.info-box li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--laterite-red); font-weight: 700; }
.info-box.highlight li::before { color: var(--gold); }
.tradition-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--bg-alt); }
.section-label { display: block; font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--saffron); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 3px; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; text-align: center; }
.tradition-story { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 420px 1fr; gap: 3rem; align-items: start; margin: 3rem 0; }
.story-image img { width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.15); }
.story-content h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.9rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.story-content p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.9; margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
.scripture-quote { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 1.8rem; border-radius: 10px; border-left: 4px solid var(--laterite-red); margin-top: 1.5rem; }
.scripture-quote p { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.25rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--laterite-dark); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
.quote-attribution { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
.tradition-variants { margin-top: 4rem; }
.tradition-variants h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 2rem; text-align: center; }
.variant-detail { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 2.5rem; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 1.8rem; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold); }
.variant-detail h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.variant-detail p { font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.pricing-section { background: var(--bg-base); padding: 5rem 2rem; }
.pricing-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 2.5rem; max-width: 1200px; margin: 3rem auto; }
.price-card { background: var(--bg-base); border-radius: 14px; box-shadow: 0 8px 35px rgba(0,0,0,0.09); overflow: hidden; position: relative; border: 2px solid var(--bg-alt); }
.price-card.featured { border: 3px solid var(--gold); }
.price-badge { position: absolute; top: 18px; right: -32px; background: var(--laterite-red); color: white; padding: 0.4rem 3rem; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; transform: rotate(45deg); }
.price-header { background: var(--laterite-dark); padding: 2.5rem 2rem; text-align: center; color: white; }
.price-card.featured .price-header { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--saffron) 0%, var(--laterite-dark) 100%); }
.price-header h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.price-amount { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: center; gap: 0.3rem; }
.currency { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
.amount { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 3.8rem; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1; }
.price-features { padding: 2rem; }
.price-features h4 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--laterite-red); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.price-features ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
.price-features li { padding: 0.7rem 0 0.7rem 1.8rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.6; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-alt); }
.price-features li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.price-features li::before { content: '✓'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--laterite-red); font-weight: 700; }
.price-cta { display: block; margin: 0 2rem 2rem; padding: 1.1rem; background: var(--laterite-red); color: white; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 2px; font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem; transition: all 0.3s ease; }
.price-cta:hover { background: var(--saffron); transform: translateY(-2px); }
.price-card.featured .price-cta { background: var(--gold); color: var(--text-muted); }
.booking-cta-section { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--laterite-red) 0%, #6b1f2b 100%); text-align: center; }
.booking-cta-container { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
.booking-cta-container h2 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 2.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: white; margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
.booking-cta-container p { font-size: 1.2rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.95); margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; }
.booking-cta-container strong { color: #ffd285; }
.booking-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 2rem; }
.btn-large { padding: 1.4rem 3.5rem; font-size: 1.15rem; }
@media (max-width: 1024px) { .content-grid, .tradition-story { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .pooja-hero h1 { font-size: 2.8rem; }
  .pooja-quick-info { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .pricing-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .booking-cta-container h2 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
  .booking-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; align-items: stretch; }
}
</style>
